        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 5:17PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles west of Cohoctah to near Fenton to near
Ortonville. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Fenton, Holly, Cohoctah, and Oak Grove around 520 PM EDT.
Oxford and Clarkston around 525 PM EDT.
Pontiac and Hartland around 535 PM EDT.
Milford and Rochester around 550 PM EDT.
Troy around 600 PM EDT.
West Bloomfield around 605 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Keego Harbor,
Waterford, Orchard Lake, Rankin, Holly State Recreation Area,
Commerce, Rose Center, Conway Township, Auburn Hills, and Lake
Angelus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
